reviews.review_text:
A show that has it all...plus a thunderous Other One 
Stranger by the mid 1980's was fully developed and was a clear signal from the band that they were here to play. 
 
1983-85 Bird Songs reached a peak that the band in later years could not match.  

Post space they play a cool Wheel intro for over 3 minutes, which has the audience engaging in hand clapping. This Wheel is powerful and the transition into a brief Playin’ Reprise is seamless and features no vocals before landing perfectly at the Other One.

The Other One and is clearly the highlight of the show as there is nearly a 2-minute opening before the first verse is sung. Jerry simply is on fire for all of this and the band continues for another ninety second before Bobby sings the first verse…this is extremely rare for any Other Ones after 1973, before dropping into a heart felt and powerful Stella Blue, and on this night, Jerry croons his heart out.

They close the night out with baby Blue, which back in 1983 was probably the best encore you could get.

Happy trails.
